Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and brown all over, stirring occasionally. This will take around ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, chop the @baby corn{60}(chopped in half widthways). Trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed and chopped into thirds) and chop into thirds. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 1cm pieces.

Add the corn, beans, pepper, @tomato puree{30%g} and @Zanzibar style curry powder{1%tbsp} to the chicken. Stir and cook for ~{2%minutes}. Stir in the water and @chicken stock powder{1%tbsp} and bring to a simmer.

Cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #foil{} and simmer until the veg are tender and the chicken is cooked though, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Cook the @steamed basmati rice{1%portion} according to the pack instructions. Meanwhile, stir the @reduced fat creme fraiche{75%g} into the curry and gently heat through until piping hot.

Divide the rice between your #bowls{}. Spoon your curry on top of your rice and enjoy!

> When you fancy a curry in a hurry, this is the recipe for you. From pan to plate in just 20 minutes, our Speedy Zanzibar Chicken Curry is creamy, rich and packed full of veg.

> Nutrition per serving: 536 kcal, 22 g fat, 8 g saturated fat, 46 g carbohydrates, 8 g sugar, 37 g protein, 1.1 g sodium. Serving size: 473g.